    <thetext>Build ID: I20070621-1340

Steps To Reproduce:
1. Open File &gt; New &gt; File
2. Click Advanced, select the checkbox and select the parent project.
3. Click Variables... &gt; New and create a link variable pointing to some directory.
4. Use the link variable to create a new link. If the linked file has a whitespace, e.g. &quot;my text.txt&quot;, than a link would look like MYDIR/my text.txt.
5. The wizard says that the resource doesn't exist, even if it is in the file system. And when Finish is pressed, a number of error messages are displayed and invalid link is created. For files without whitespace the wizard works OK.</thetext>
